events.message:
Avoid recalculating vchKeyedNetGroup in eviction logic.

Lazy calculate vchKeyedNetGroup in CNode::GetKeyedNetGroup.
Support SipHash with arbitrary byte writes
Use 64-bit SipHash of netgroups in eviction

test: Add more test vectors for siphash

events.body: May want to re-title this PR

The original had grown in scope anyway, it now does:
- Extend the SipHash implementation
- Improved comments
- Added tests
- Switched to thread-safe random seed initializers
- Switch node eviction to use siphash

rename.from: test: Add more test vectors for siphash

events.body: tACK on the purely Siphash part (reimplemented this PR tests included into NBitcoin successfully on https://github.com/MetacoSA/NBitcoin/commit/c915829c0e4595d49c357525c9c51b4cb52f4b7f)

#8086 had plenty of ACKs and this did only add tests, which also got ACKs.

You complained in #8086 about it being insecure. If you can explain how,
I'll gladly revert the siphash-for-eviction part.

@sipa it's not clear who or what you're replying to

In any case, it was time to merge this, there were no concrete concerns left.
